Former president Thabo Mbeki says struggle stalwart Andrew Mlangeni was deeply concerned about the rot in the ANC. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former president Thabo Mbeki says struggle stalwart Andrew Mlangeni was deeply concerned about the rot in the ANC. He was paying a virtual tribute to Mlangeni. WATCH: Andrew Mlangeni remembered Mbeki said the ANC needs to honour Mlangeni by committing to the renewal of the ANC. Mlangeni spent over two decades on Robben Island after he was convicted at the Rivonia Treason trial in 1964.